WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.959 --> 00:00:02.799
speaker: How fares Prince
Daemon with our army?

2
00:00:03.128 --> 00:00:05.005
There has been no word.

3
00:00:07.799 --> 00:00:08.925
(dragon growls)

4
00:00:09.134 --> 00:00:10.969
♪ (tense music plays) ♪

5
00:00:11.094 --> 00:00:13.762
Your false queen
Rhaenyra is a kinslayer.

6
00:00:13.763 --> 00:00:14.848
Cunts!

7
00:00:15.473 --> 00:00:17.474
Rhaenys Targaryen: <i>Soon.
they will not even remember</i>

8
00:00:17.475 --> 00:00:19.185
what began the war
in the first place.

9
00:00:19.853 --> 00:00:21.622
Criston Cole: <i>The Riverlands
are the key to the war.</i>

10
00:00:21.646 --> 00:00:23.481
Harrenhal is the key
to the Riverlands.

11
00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:27.485
I'm claiming Harrenhal.

12
00:00:27.652 --> 00:00:28.653
Apparently so.

13
00:00:28.987 --> 00:00:33.825
I Ser Simon Strong pledge fealty
to Rhaenyra of House Targaryen.

14
00:00:34.492 --> 00:00:36.661
- (exhales softly)
- Ser Criston.

15
00:00:36.786 --> 00:00:38.829
May I present my brother.
Ser Gwayne Hightower.

16
00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:39.831
Ser Criston.

17
00:00:40.665 --> 00:00:43.269
Alicent Hightower: <i>Ser Gwayne has
volunteered to accompany you into battle.</i>

18
00:00:43.293 --> 00:00:45.670
(roars)

19
00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:49.341
A good showing. Ser Criston.

20
00:00:49.883 --> 00:00:52.343
Lord Larys. my
father always said

21
00:00:52.344 --> 00:00:54.887
he had no use for a
master of whisperers.

22
00:00:54.888 --> 00:00:56.890
I find myself wanting for one.

23
00:00:57.015 --> 00:00:58.391
You honor me. Your Grace.

24
00:00:58.892 --> 00:01:00.184
They tell me that you're the one

25
00:01:00.185 --> 00:01:01.852
that dragged my
body out of the sea.

26
00:01:01.853 --> 00:01:03.646
I am indebted to you. Alyn.

27
00:01:03.855 --> 00:01:04.856
All hail the king!

28
00:01:04.981 --> 00:01:06.232
patrons: All hail the king!

29
00:01:06.358 --> 00:01:08.568
(laughs hysterically)

30
00:01:08.693 --> 00:01:09.735
Aemond the Fierce!

31
00:01:09.736 --> 00:01:12.238
And yet you still lie
with your very first.

32
00:01:12.405 --> 00:01:13.405
(cackles)

33
00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:16.368
What do you know of the
movements of Alicent Hightower?

34
00:01:16.659 --> 00:01:19.579
<i>If war can be averted. it
is my duty to avert it.</i>

35
00:01:19.871 --> 00:01:22.832
♪ (thrilling music plays) ♪

36
00:01:24.417 --> 00:01:25.085
(gasps)

37
00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:26.670
I must speak with you.

38
00:01:26.878 --> 00:01:28.421
<i>I saw the king that night.</i>

39
00:01:28.672 --> 00:01:30.382
<i>Did you betray him
at the very last?</i>

40
00:01:30.507 --> 00:01:32.592
I have been at times
unkind but never untrue.

41
00:01:32.717 --> 00:01:34.437
But he spoke Aegon's
name. He said he was...

42
00:01:34.552 --> 00:01:37.055
The prince that was
promised to unite the realm.

43
00:01:37.597 --> 00:01:39.724
He spoke to you of The
Song of Ice and Fire?

44
00:01:39.849 --> 00:01:41.935
Do you think me capable
of such naked deceit?

45
00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:43.394
A terrible war is looming.

46
00:01:43.395 --> 00:01:44.771
<i>And even victory
may be so bloody</i>

47
00:01:44.896 --> 00:01:46.021
as to be counted a loss.

48
00:01:46.022 --> 00:01:48.607
There has been no mistake.
It's too late. Rhaenyra.

49
00:01:48.608 --> 00:01:49.693
Alicent.

50
00:01:54.447 --> 00:01:56.908
Young Rhaenyra Targaryen: Always
coming and going. aren't you?

51
00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:59.577
And I have to clean
up afterwards.

52
00:02:10.046 --> 00:02:13.216
(epic theme playing)

53
00:02:51.796 --> 00:02:53.965
♪

54
00:03:36.299 --> 00:03:38.510
♪

55
00:03:53.983 --> 00:03:56.319
(music fades out)

56
00:03:57.904 --> 00:04:00.907
(ominous music playing)

57
00:04:01.700 --> 00:04:03.702
(door creaking)

58
00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:13.003
(footsteps echoing)

59
00:04:20.719 --> 00:04:24.097
(woman speaking High
Valyrian. voice echoing)

60
00:04:32.188 --> 00:04:33.106
What?

61
00:04:33.107 --> 00:04:35.900
(High Valyrian continues)

62
00:04:38.069 --> 00:04:39.904
I can't understand.

63
00:04:44.242 --> 00:04:46.953
(speaking High Valyrian)

64
00:04:50.915 --> 00:04:52.584
Speak plainly.

65
00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.090
Stop.

66
00:04:59.924 --> 00:05:01.384
Stop it.

67
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:12.144
(tense music playing)

68
00:05:12.145 --> 00:05:14.564
(crown clattering)

69
00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.611
(sword falls)

70
00:05:25.950 --> 00:05:27.952
♪

71
00:05:33.083 --> 00:05:36.086
- (distorted) There's been a raven.
- (door opens)

72
00:05:39.589 --> 00:05:42.383
Simon Strong:
Good morrow. Your Grace.

73
00:05:42.384 --> 00:05:45.303
Slept well. I trust?

74
00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:48.431
As I said. there's been a raven.

75
00:05:50.308 --> 00:05:53.769
Aegon's army departed King's
Landing a fortnight ago.

76
00:05:53.770 --> 00:05:57.064
The castles of
Rosby and Stokeworth

77
00:05:57.065 --> 00:05:58.650
have both fallen without siege.

78
00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:00.984
They have raised Aegon's banner

79
00:06:00.985 --> 00:06:04.781
and added their levies to
Ser Criston Cole's host.

80
00:06:05.532 --> 00:06:08.033
Both houses cited that

81
00:06:08.034 --> 00:06:11.996
sad business with the usurper's
son in their declarations.

82
00:06:13.039 --> 00:06:15.207
Ser Criston's army.

83
00:06:15.208 --> 00:06:17.626
now tripled in strength.

84
00:06:17.627 --> 00:06:20.337
might have Harrenhal
as its destination.

85
00:06:20.338 --> 00:06:23.841
- (goat bleats) - Even if you
can raise a host of Rivermen.

86
00:06:23.842 --> 00:06:27.053
they will not be ready
in time to face him.

87
00:06:33.018 --> 00:06:36.146
Let's see what your Lord
Paramount is made of.

88
00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:38.815
(sighs)

89
00:06:41.651 --> 00:06:45.029
(stammers) My prince...
Uh. My-My Grace.

90
00:06:45.030 --> 00:06:46.406
Your Grace.

91
00:06:47.157 --> 00:06:50.368
Lord Grover is looking more hale
and healthy than I expected.

92
00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:52.036
Uh. this is Ser Oscar Tully.

93
00:06:52.037 --> 00:06:53.204
grandson to Grover Tully.

94
00:06:53.329 --> 00:06:54.747
He is heir to Riverrun

95
00:06:54.748 --> 00:06:57.875
and the future Lord
Paramount of the Riverlands.

96
00:06:57.876 --> 00:07:01.295
His Grace. the King
Consort. Daemon Targaryen.

97
00:07:01.296 --> 00:07:04.883
- Oscar Tully: It is an honor. Your Grace.
- Daemon Targaryen: Indeed.

98
00:07:05.008 --> 00:07:07.010
(sword clatters)

99
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.891
How fares your grandsire?

100
00:07:16.686 --> 00:07:19.897
Sadly. he remains incapacitated.

101
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:22.649
He lies in a kind
of waking sleep.

102
00:07:22.650 --> 00:07:26.278
unable to do much more
than take meager drink.

103
00:07:26.279 --> 00:07:28.947
It is barely enough
to sustain him.

104
00:07:28.948 --> 00:07:30.657
So. he's alive?

105
00:07:30.658 --> 00:07:32.951
Yes. gods be good.

106
00:07:32.952 --> 00:07:35.747
Well. my time is short and
I have need of an army.

107
00:07:35.872 --> 00:07:37.998
Perhaps you might place a
feather pillow over his head

108
00:07:37.999 --> 00:07:40.710
and speed along
your inheritance?

109
00:07:42.545 --> 00:07:46.257
I-I love my grandsire.
like a father.

110
00:07:46.883 --> 00:07:50.553
My own lord father died
suddenly. himself a young man.

111
00:07:51.096 --> 00:07:53.932
Lord Grover raised
me in his stead.

112
00:07:54.057 --> 00:07:55.057
All very touching.

113
00:07:55.058 --> 00:07:57.059
Are you here to speak with
your grandsire's voice?

114
00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:59.269
For House Tully
and the Riverlands?

115
00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:00.939
While he still lives?

116
00:08:03.274 --> 00:08:07.278
- That is not our way.
- Then you're of no use to me.

117
00:08:07.779 --> 00:08:09.613
I can see why the
Blackwoods and the Brackens

118
00:08:09.614 --> 00:08:10.864
did not fear to start a war

119
00:08:10.865 --> 00:08:13.367
beneath the nose of
their liege lords.

120
00:08:13.368 --> 00:08:15.619
House Tully is a
fish with no head.

121
00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:17.871
Remind me which
of your countrymen

122
00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:19.623
claim to fight in
the name of Aegon?

123
00:08:19.624 --> 00:08:21.792
Was it. was it
Bracken or Blackwood?

124
00:08:21.793 --> 00:08:24.545
It was House Bracken that
declared Green. Your Grace.

125
00:08:24.546 --> 00:08:25.964
Who could remember.

126
00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:27.882
Summon the Blackwoods here.

127
00:08:27.883 --> 00:08:29.134
I require men of action

128
00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:31.261
to lead my host of Rivermen.

129
00:08:31.594 --> 00:08:34.305
(tense music playing)

130
00:08:38.143 --> 00:08:40.186
(indistinct chatter)

131
00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:42.772
(dog barking)

132
00:08:45.442 --> 00:08:47.610
♪

133
00:08:54.159 --> 00:08:56.161
(birds cawing)

134
00:09:00.123 --> 00:09:01.666
M'lady.

135
00:09:04.878 --> 00:09:08.630
"Princess." if we're
holding to formalities.

136
00:09:08.631 --> 00:09:11.384
Apologies. Princess.

137
00:09:12.677 --> 00:09:15.180
And you are Alyn.

138
00:09:15.305 --> 00:09:17.640
Yes. Princess.

139
00:09:18.725 --> 00:09:20.392
I'm given to understand
my lord husband

140
00:09:20.393 --> 00:09:22.354
owes you his life.

141
00:09:25.315 --> 00:09:28.818
But I was not told his
savior was so comely.

142
00:09:29.736 --> 00:09:32.154
Your mother must've
been very beautiful.

143
00:09:32.155 --> 00:09:34.866
- Corlys Velaryon: Rhaenys.
- (clears throat)

144
00:09:42.040 --> 00:09:44.918
- Is your work finished?
- No. m'lord.

145
00:09:48.213 --> 00:09:50.215
(indistinct chatter)

146
00:09:55.679 --> 00:09:57.889
I just had a word
with your captains.

147
00:09:59.557 --> 00:10:03.269
He was the sailor who plucked
you from your watery grave?

148
00:10:04.396 --> 00:10:06.398
(birds cawing)

149
00:10:11.027 --> 00:10:12.028
Yes.

150
00:10:13.196 --> 00:10:15.115
You did not think to mention it?

151
00:10:15.907 --> 00:10:17.909
I did not think it relevant.

152
00:10:19.911 --> 00:10:22.122
I know who he is. Corlys.

153
00:10:24.416 --> 00:10:27.918
Alyn's past is no fault of his.

154
00:10:27.919 --> 00:10:29.003
He saved his lord's life.

155
00:10:29.004 --> 00:10:30.422
He should be raised
up and honored.

156
00:10:30.547 --> 00:10:31.672
not hidden beneath the tides.

157
00:10:31.673 --> 00:10:33.925
Is this why you came?

158
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:36.803
To subject me to an inquisition?

159
00:10:38.555 --> 00:10:42.599
I came to tell you that Baela
has called me to Dragonstone.

160
00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:44.060
Baela?

161
00:10:44.936 --> 00:10:47.605
That council is going to dine
on her and Jace for supper.

162
00:10:47.731 --> 00:10:49.773
They grow restless in
Rhaenyra's absence.

163
00:10:49.774 --> 00:10:53.110
Still... Where has
that woman gone?

164
00:10:53.111 --> 00:10:57.073
I suspect to try and draw
us all back from the abyss.

165
00:11:09.085 --> 00:11:11.963
- (knocks at door)
- (Alicent sighs)

166
00:11:14.424 --> 00:11:16.426
(distant chatter)

167
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:22.307
- Good morrow. Your Grace.
- Good morrow. Grand Maester.

168
00:11:26.144 --> 00:11:28.562
As requested.

169
00:11:28.563 --> 00:11:32.066
- I brewed it myself.
- Thank you.

170
00:11:32.067 --> 00:11:34.444
I will see it
delivered discreetly.

171
00:11:35.528 --> 00:11:39.865
Do report if the recipient
has need of any remedy.

172
00:11:39.866 --> 00:11:42.452
The tea is known to
disagree with the gut.

173
00:11:43.119 --> 00:11:45.455
I shall observe
the girl closely.

174
00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:49.000
(birds chirping)

175
00:11:51.878 --> 00:11:53.797
Grand Maester.

176
00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:01.887
You've ever been
a practical man.

177
00:12:01.888 --> 00:12:04.516
an honorable servant
to the crown.

178
00:12:05.141 --> 00:12:08.520
And you served my lord
husband in his darkest hours.

179
00:12:08.853 --> 00:12:11.231
Such was my duty. Your Grace.

180
00:12:12.565 --> 00:12:13.983
Tell me.

181
00:12:15.985 --> 00:12:19.197
Do you believe Viserys
wanted Aegon to succeed him?

182
00:12:19.322 --> 00:12:21.324
(birds chirping)

183
00:12:23.660 --> 00:12:25.995
I could not know.

184
00:12:27.706 --> 00:12:30.917
His Grace never raised
the matter with me.

185
00:12:43.430 --> 00:12:45.432
(distant chatter)

186
00:12:46.683 --> 00:12:48.893
(door closes)

187
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:52.605
(tense music playing)

188
00:13:10.248 --> 00:13:12.250
♪

189
00:13:15.754 --> 00:13:17.255
(groans)

190
00:13:22.594 --> 00:13:24.137
(groans)

191
00:13:25.305 --> 00:13:26.639
(coughs)

192
00:13:30.226 --> 00:13:31.685
Baela Targaryen: Ser
Criston Cole's host

193
00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:33.228
has taken to exploiting
the tree cover

194
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:34.646
to conceal its movements.

195
00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:36.190
He now only travels by night

196
00:13:36.191 --> 00:13:37.442
to confound our dragons.

197
00:13:37.567 --> 00:13:39.443
Bartimos Celtigar: And
what is Cole's heading?

198
00:13:39.444 --> 00:13:41.070
It is difficult to say.
but there were signs

199
00:13:41.071 --> 00:13:44.115
of an army moving
northwest. I believe.

200
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:45.491
Gormon Massey:
(laughs) She believes.

201
00:13:45.492 --> 00:13:47.785
You should've burned them
when you had the chance.

202
00:13:47.786 --> 00:13:48.911
Perhaps you can. Ser Alfred.

203
00:13:48.912 --> 00:13:50.412
when you next sight
them on your dragon.

204
00:13:50.413 --> 00:13:53.874
- (slight chuckle) - The only
reason we know any of this

205
00:13:53.875 --> 00:13:55.376
is because of Baela's efforts.

206
00:13:55.377 --> 00:13:57.086
Bartimos: What do
we know. my prince?

207
00:13:57.087 --> 00:13:59.421
If you ask me. it
is little and less.

208
00:13:59.422 --> 00:14:02.216
We know that Cole possesses a
host that is growing in strength

209
00:14:02.217 --> 00:14:03.467
and that it is a problem.

210
00:14:03.468 --> 00:14:04.968
Gormon: Can Daemon
hope to meet it

211
00:14:04.969 --> 00:14:06.595
with his own in time?

212
00:14:06.596 --> 00:14:07.555
And if I know the Riverlands.

213
00:14:07.556 --> 00:14:09.808
he has more disentangling
ahead of him

214
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:12.977
than the end of a Lyseni orgy.

215
00:14:13.103 --> 00:14:16.648
Have you heard word
from your father?

216
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:22.487
- No. - Maester Gerardys:
Ravens were sent to Harrenhal

217
00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:25.823
seeking news of Daemon's
progress with the Riverlords.

218
00:14:25.824 --> 00:14:28.159
None have. as yet. returned.

219
00:14:28.284 --> 00:14:29.868
Alfred Broome: Just so.

220
00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:32.246
An enemy host. growing
in constitution.

221
00:14:32.247 --> 00:14:37.167
marches somewhere in the
vastness of the Crownlands.

222
00:14:37.168 --> 00:14:40.879
We could. perhaps. act if
only we had a host of our own.

223
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:42.465
Or someone here to lead us.

224
00:14:42.966 --> 00:14:45.051
Mind your tongue. Ser Alfred.

225
00:14:46.302 --> 00:14:48.762
Does it speak
falsely. my prince?

226
00:14:48.763 --> 00:14:51.140
This council is rudderless.

227
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:53.643
I'm doing my best to
steer it. Ser Alfred.

228
00:14:54.853 --> 00:14:58.772
Why should your voice be any
louder than ours. Princess?

229
00:14:58.773 --> 00:15:00.524
The queen did not name you Hand.

230
00:15:00.525 --> 00:15:03.068
It is her voice. and
that of the king consort.

231
00:15:03.069 --> 00:15:06.321
that we need to raise alliances
and command our vassals.

232
00:15:06.322 --> 00:15:09.743
- But they are gone.
- Corlys: What has come of this council?

233
00:15:10.535 --> 00:15:11.703
(soft gasp)

234
00:15:14.831 --> 00:15:16.332
My lord.

235
00:15:19.169 --> 00:15:22.421
Our enemy is on the march.

236
00:15:22.422 --> 00:15:24.716
Is there naught to be done
in the absence of the queen.

237
00:15:24.841 --> 00:15:28.010
but to grouse and
claw for power?

238
00:15:28.011 --> 00:15:30.180
(Bartimos sighs)

239
00:15:34.100 --> 00:15:37.519
We do not know the
queen's doings.

240
00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:40.147
But we must trust that
she seeks the same

241
00:15:40.148 --> 00:15:42.442
as each of us at this table.

242
00:15:43.943 --> 00:15:46.529
An end to this conflict.

243
00:15:48.406 --> 00:15:51.743
- (rain pattering)
- (tense music playing)

244
00:15:53.036 --> 00:15:55.205
(birds cawing)

245
00:15:59.918 --> 00:16:02.087
(indistinct shouting)

246
00:16:05.590 --> 00:16:08.093
(distant yell)

247
00:16:08.218 --> 00:16:10.552
Criston Cole:
Men of House Darklyn.

248
00:16:10.553 --> 00:16:14.891
All who bend the knee to the
true king. Aegon. will be spared.

249
00:16:15.767 --> 00:16:18.603
You can earn back your
honor by raising his banner

250
00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:20.312
and fighting in his name

251
00:16:20.313 --> 00:16:23.274
against the Whore
of Dragonstone.

252
00:16:24.067 --> 00:16:26.277
All who refuse...

253
00:16:27.612 --> 00:16:29.614
will have their death.

254
00:16:31.408 --> 00:16:33.785
♪

255
00:16:43.670 --> 00:16:45.171
Good morrow. Lord Darklyn.

256
00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:49.300
Is there no honor left
in this world. Cole?

257
00:16:49.426 --> 00:16:51.343
Sacking your queen's own castles

258
00:16:51.344 --> 00:16:54.388
and putting her
people to the sword?

259
00:16:54.389 --> 00:16:56.141
"Kingmaker."

260
00:17:00.270 --> 00:17:02.772
You are not fit for
the white cloak.

261
00:17:04.149 --> 00:17:06.108
♪

262
00:17:06.109 --> 00:17:09.362
This is a better death
than a traitor deserves.

263
00:17:09.779 --> 00:17:12.157
You should thank me for it.

264
00:17:14.034 --> 00:17:17.287
Yours will come in kind.

265
00:17:19.122 --> 00:17:20.498
(grunts)

266
00:17:22.834 --> 00:17:24.836
(horse neighs)

267
00:17:28.006 --> 00:17:30.216
♪

268
00:17:31.676 --> 00:17:32.844
Lord Hand.

269
00:17:48.234 --> 00:17:50.362
We'll lead the van northeast.

270
00:17:50.487 --> 00:17:51.945
follow the coastline.

271
00:17:51.946 --> 00:17:53.322
(horse neighs)

272
00:17:53.323 --> 00:17:54.865
I realize you were
neither born nor bred

273
00:17:54.866 --> 00:17:58.369
anywhere near the Crownlands.
my good Lord Hand.

274
00:17:58.370 --> 00:18:01.164
but Harrenhal is to the west.

275
00:18:05.001 --> 00:18:06.711
Indeed it is.

276
00:18:09.381 --> 00:18:12.717
Fuck you. I told you we
should've sent our dragons.

277
00:18:12.842 --> 00:18:14.511
And now look what's happened.

278
00:18:14.844 --> 00:18:17.638
Daemon. of all people.
has taken Harrenhal.

279
00:18:17.639 --> 00:18:20.224
I give you a job. and
now you just sit there.

280
00:18:20.225 --> 00:18:22.852
It's your fucking castle!

281
00:18:24.396 --> 00:18:28.566
Well. that castle is more
crippled than I am. Your Grace.

282
00:18:28.692 --> 00:18:29.609
(scoffs)

283
00:18:29.610 --> 00:18:31.193
It's like to drive
Daemon to madness

284
00:18:31.194 --> 00:18:32.736
as he attempts to
make use of it.

285
00:18:32.737 --> 00:18:35.073
It is beyond his faculties.

286
00:18:35.699 --> 00:18:39.660
It is also penniless. as I
happily control all of its gold.

287
00:18:39.661 --> 00:18:43.372
So. as Harrenhal saps
Daemon's resolve.

288
00:18:43.373 --> 00:18:45.749
the false queen remains
trapped on her island.

289
00:18:45.750 --> 00:18:49.211
and Ser Criston continues felling
castles in the Crownlands.

290
00:18:49.212 --> 00:18:51.256
(stammers) Wh...

291
00:18:51.631 --> 00:18:54.425
I need to be informed
of these things

292
00:18:54.426 --> 00:18:56.094
if I am to make
informed rulings.

293
00:18:56.219 --> 00:18:57.845
I will not be made to
look a fool in front of

294
00:18:57.846 --> 00:19:00.890
- my allies and enemies.
- Aemond Targaryen: Harrenhal must wait.

295
00:19:04.269 --> 00:19:06.896
Ser Criston is marching
on Rook's Rest.

296
00:19:07.439 --> 00:19:09.231
Rook's Re... A pathetic prize.

297
00:19:09.232 --> 00:19:11.609
- I gave no such command...
- The castle is small.

298
00:19:12.736 --> 00:19:13.777
weakly defended.

299
00:19:13.778 --> 00:19:17.031
and Lord Staunton sits
on Rhaenyra's council.

300
00:19:17.032 --> 00:19:19.199
After Cole smashes it.

301
00:19:19.200 --> 00:19:21.745
we'll have Dragonstone
effectively cut off by land.

302
00:19:23.288 --> 00:19:25.873
This war will not be
won with dragons alone.

303
00:19:25.874 --> 00:19:29.168
but with dragons flying
behind armies of men.

304
00:19:29.169 --> 00:19:34.173
No! Have him turn about.
I want Harrenhal back.

305
00:19:34.174 --> 00:19:36.634
Cole is already
preparing his attack.

306
00:19:37.969 --> 00:19:39.970
Uh. how-how do you know this?

307
00:19:39.971 --> 00:19:42.015
Aemond: He sent word to me.

308
00:19:42.974 --> 00:19:44.351
To you?

309
00:19:46.978 --> 00:19:49.272
The two of you have been

310
00:19:49.606 --> 00:19:54.026
plotting... without
my authority?

311
00:19:54.027 --> 00:19:55.487
(sighs)

312
00:19:57.822 --> 00:20:00.533
(speaking High Valyrian)

313
00:20:14.798 --> 00:20:15.840
Mm.

314
00:20:33.358 --> 00:20:35.527
(birds cawing)

315
00:20:39.030 --> 00:20:41.700
(speaking High Valyrian)

316
00:20:49.582 --> 00:20:50.583
Mm.

317
00:20:52.711 --> 00:20:54.921
(councilmember clears throat)

318
00:20:56.381 --> 00:20:58.590
Harrenhal is a useful morass.

319
00:20:58.591 --> 00:21:01.553
It will keep Daemon well-occupied
while we strengthen our host

320
00:21:01.678 --> 00:21:03.804
and weaken Rhaenyra's
support on the mainland.

321
00:21:03.805 --> 00:21:06.807
We will deal with it in
the Riverlands in time.

322
00:21:06.808 --> 00:21:11.311
But right now. Rook's
Rest is an easy target

323
00:21:11.312 --> 00:21:13.565
and a worthy effort.

324
00:21:14.399 --> 00:21:17.401
Don't you agree. my king?

325
00:21:17.402 --> 00:21:20.697
(tense music playing)

326
00:21:28.246 --> 00:21:30.372
(knocks on door)

327
00:21:30.373 --> 00:21:33.626
- (heavy breathing)
- Come.

328
00:21:37.922 --> 00:21:39.632
Lord Larys.

329
00:21:43.303 --> 00:21:45.346
I thought I'd look in
on you. Your Grace.

330
00:21:45.347 --> 00:21:48.266
after your absence
from the small council.

331
00:21:48.391 --> 00:21:50.309
I feared something was amiss.

332
00:21:50.310 --> 00:21:53.354
(sighs) You're kind
to do so. my lord.

333
00:21:53.355 --> 00:21:55.856
but indulgence was my sin.

334
00:21:55.857 --> 00:21:59.276
I... ventured into the lamprey
pie at last night's supper.

335
00:21:59.277 --> 00:22:01.195
Too far. I fear.

336
00:22:01.196 --> 00:22:03.448
(heavy breathing)

337
00:22:04.324 --> 00:22:06.076
Larys Strong: Mm.

338
00:22:07.619 --> 00:22:10.121
That is a rich indulgence.

339
00:22:10.830 --> 00:22:14.500
But I believe it is a sin
to deny your appetites.

340
00:22:14.501 --> 00:22:17.962
They are what make us
fully alive as mortal men.

341
00:22:21.966 --> 00:22:24.469
Was anything of note
discussed at the council?

342
00:22:24.594 --> 00:22:26.470
Daemon having seized Harrenhal

343
00:22:26.471 --> 00:22:29.140
and His Grace's
resulting displeasure.

344
00:22:29.265 --> 00:22:34.311
I would've thought you would
be the most aggrieved. my lord.

345
00:22:34.312 --> 00:22:36.773
I see it as a loss
for our greater good.

346
00:22:37.982 --> 00:22:40.275
Dragonstone's attentions
are greatly divided.

347
00:22:40.276 --> 00:22:43.863
First in the Riverlands and the
Gullet. and now the Crownlands.

348
00:22:44.656 --> 00:22:46.573
Ser Criston wins every
challenge he faces there.

349
00:22:46.574 --> 00:22:50.161
That truth alone is like
to incite Rhaenyra's fury.

350
00:22:50.787 --> 00:22:53.665
He's covered himself
in glory. to be sure.

351
00:22:54.624 --> 00:22:57.293
And you must worry for him?

352
00:22:57.544 --> 00:22:59.963
Your sworn sword...

353
00:23:00.964 --> 00:23:02.506
on the march.

354
00:23:02.507 --> 00:23:03.675
ever exposed to dragons?

355
00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:05.969
It is a perilous road.

356
00:23:09.014 --> 00:23:11.224
Ser Criston is the
Hand of the King.

357
00:23:12.308 --> 00:23:15.186
We should all pray for his
victory and safe return.

358
00:23:16.312 --> 00:23:17.647
Indeed.

359
00:23:19.149 --> 00:23:22.151
(sighs. inhales)

360
00:23:22.152 --> 00:23:25.196
- (Larys grunts)
- (Alicent sighs)

361
00:23:27.407 --> 00:23:30.994
If I may be so bold. my queen...

362
00:23:36.541 --> 00:23:39.044
you have not seemed
yourself of late.

363
00:23:40.503 --> 00:23:42.714
Only weeks ago. my
lord husband was alive

364
00:23:42.839 --> 00:23:44.841
and the realm was at peace.

365
00:23:45.175 --> 00:23:49.094
Now. I've... barely had the
hours to grieve one tragedy

366
00:23:49.095 --> 00:23:50.013
before suffering the next.

367
00:23:50.014 --> 00:23:54.017
I regret if I have
not been myself.

368
00:23:56.061 --> 00:23:57.061
Hm.

369
00:23:57.228 --> 00:24:00.190
I did not know you shared
your lord husband's love...

370
00:24:01.232 --> 00:24:04.151
for the histories.

371
00:24:04.152 --> 00:24:08.947
If not his love. then certainly
an... an abiding interest.

372
00:24:08.948 --> 00:24:10.783
The voices of history
guided Viserys.

373
00:24:10.784 --> 00:24:12.743
He knew that his wisdom alone

374
00:24:12.744 --> 00:24:13.912
could only reach so far.

375
00:24:14.204 --> 00:24:17.040
Do you think that is why
he changed his mind...

376
00:24:18.291 --> 00:24:19.876
in the end?

377
00:24:20.794 --> 00:24:24.713
No matter how suited he
thought Rhaenyra for the crown.

378
00:24:24.714 --> 00:24:29.426
the. uh. voices of
history. as you say.

379
00:24:29.427 --> 00:24:32.097
would have told him how
the realm would react

380
00:24:32.222 --> 00:24:34.682
- to her succession.
- It was impossible to know what steered his thoughts

381
00:24:34.683 --> 00:24:36.810
in those final hours.

382
00:24:37.811 --> 00:24:40.230
Do you now doubt his intentions?

383
00:24:42.232 --> 00:24:43.608
(sniffles)

384
00:24:45.402 --> 00:24:47.695
(light. tense music playing)

385
00:24:47.696 --> 00:24:51.115
Rhaenyra's supporters will
believe what they wish.

386
00:24:51.116 --> 00:24:53.159
And so will Aegon's.

387
00:24:53.827 --> 00:24:58.205
The war will be fought.
many will die...

388
00:24:58.206 --> 00:25:01.167
and the victor will
eventually ascend the throne.

389
00:25:02.919 --> 00:25:06.798
The significance of Viserys's
intentions died with him.

390
00:25:08.258 --> 00:25:10.260
♪

391
00:25:12.762 --> 00:25:14.931
Yes. it did.

392
00:25:20.020 --> 00:25:21.771
(rain pattering)

393
00:25:26.151 --> 00:25:28.153
(water dripping)

394
00:25:39.456 --> 00:25:42.625
- (indistinct shouting)
- (footsteps)

395
00:25:48.340 --> 00:25:51.217
- (sword unsheathes)
- (grunts)

396
00:25:53.803 --> 00:25:56.014
(heavy breathing)

397
00:25:58.516 --> 00:26:00.185
(footsteps)

398
00:26:02.187 --> 00:26:05.190
(ominous music playing)

399
00:26:17.660 --> 00:26:19.329
(footsteps)

400
00:26:22.582 --> 00:26:24.334
(rain pattering)

401
00:26:27.754 --> 00:26:30.006
(torch clatters)

402
00:26:35.762 --> 00:26:38.014
(eerie sounds)

403
00:26:45.522 --> 00:26:47.691
(heavy breathing)

404
00:26:49.776 --> 00:26:51.403
(frog ribbits)

405
00:26:51.528 --> 00:26:54.154
It's a touch late to be
stalkin' about a strange castle.

406
00:26:54.155 --> 00:26:56.448
putting its people to the sword.

407
00:26:56.449 --> 00:26:57.909
You.

408
00:26:58.868 --> 00:27:01.328
I'm called Alys.

409
00:27:01.329 --> 00:27:02.914
Daemon: Strong?

410
00:27:03.039 --> 00:27:04.124
Rivers.

411
00:27:05.208 --> 00:27:06.208
A bastard.

412
00:27:06.584 --> 00:27:09.254
Once you get to know me.
you'll find I'm not so bad.

413
00:27:09.879 --> 00:27:14.425
- So what are you then? Some kind of maester?
- In a manner of speaking.

414
00:27:14.426 --> 00:27:18.137
I inherited the duties after
the last one fled in the night.

415
00:27:18.138 --> 00:27:21.391
- Fled? Why?
- Just never settled in.

416
00:27:22.392 --> 00:27:23.560
(chuckles)

417
00:27:23.935 --> 00:27:25.937
How are you settling in?

418
00:27:26.479 --> 00:27:29.816
I've come to know the face
of tortured rest well enough.

419
00:27:30.316 --> 00:27:34.237
Sleep can be...
thin in this place.

420
00:27:34.904 --> 00:27:37.115
What would you know of my sleep?

421
00:27:38.074 --> 00:27:41.453
Harrenhal's been cursed since
its first stone was laid.

422
00:27:42.287 --> 00:27:44.789
Black Harren felled the
grove of weirwood trees

423
00:27:44.914 --> 00:27:46.958
that grew on these lands.

424
00:27:47.083 --> 00:27:49.376
Heart trees. imbued with
the spirits of those

425
00:27:49.377 --> 00:27:51.253
who lived long before he came.

426
00:27:51.254 --> 00:27:55.049
- It's said their whispers can still be heard sometimes.
- A midwife's tale.

427
00:27:55.050 --> 00:27:59.012
Mm. the very bed you sleep in
was made from such a heart tree.

428
00:28:00.430 --> 00:28:04.267
Have you experienced
anything... of note?

429
00:28:04.768 --> 00:28:07.312
You are a strange kind of woman.

430
00:28:07.645 --> 00:28:10.439
I'm no woman at
all. I'm a barn owl.

431
00:28:10.440 --> 00:28:12.484
Cursed to live in human form.

432
00:28:13.651 --> 00:28:18.322
(chuckles) So. you've come here
after quarreling with your wife?

433
00:28:18.323 --> 00:28:19.449
What?

434
00:28:20.700 --> 00:28:23.369
You arrive here alone
to claim the castle

435
00:28:23.370 --> 00:28:25.830
and yet. send no ravens.

436
00:28:27.791 --> 00:28:30.502
Do you now plan to
make your own claim?

437
00:28:30.960 --> 00:28:33.045
- Perhaps to prove yourself to her.
- Do not try me

438
00:28:33.046 --> 00:28:35.006
with your insolence. witch.

439
00:28:35.131 --> 00:28:36.965
It's a hard thing.
I imagine. to give

440
00:28:36.966 --> 00:28:40.345
obeisance to one who
replaced you as heir.

441
00:28:42.681 --> 00:28:45.182
And a woman too. A...

442
00:28:45.183 --> 00:28:48.144
girl child you
bounced on your knee.

443
00:28:50.230 --> 00:28:53.023
I mean. does it please you that
her legitimacy is contested?

444
00:28:53.024 --> 00:28:55.109
As you stand here...

445
00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:57.778
with a castle and a dragon...

446
00:28:57.779 --> 00:29:00.198
attempting to draw
an army of men.

447
00:29:05.328 --> 00:29:06.996
Here. Drink this.

448
00:29:08.540 --> 00:29:12.419
You'll need your sleep if you're
to win this place to your side.

449
00:29:14.421 --> 00:29:16.423
♪

450
00:29:19.217 --> 00:29:20.552
(swallows)

451
00:29:21.678 --> 00:29:23.303
Willem Blackwood: (muffled)
I now rule my house as regent

452
00:29:23.304 --> 00:29:25.390
until my nephew
Benjicot comes of age.

453
00:29:30.729 --> 00:29:33.731
The Brackens are venal cravens.

454
00:29:33.732 --> 00:29:35.024
and they must pay
for their treachery

455
00:29:35.025 --> 00:29:37.444
against the laws
of gods and men.

456
00:29:38.611 --> 00:29:40.612
(normal) And against the crown.

457
00:29:40.613 --> 00:29:42.072
Who are you?

458
00:29:42.073 --> 00:29:43.782
Simon: Ser Willem Blackwood
of House Blackwood.

459
00:29:43.783 --> 00:29:47.078
Your Grace. as I said.

460
00:29:50.749 --> 00:29:52.083
Well met.

461
00:29:52.917 --> 00:29:54.753
What might I do for you?

462
00:29:54.878 --> 00:29:58.505
It was you who summoned
me. Your Grace.

463
00:29:58.506 --> 00:30:00.091
I was given to understand

464
00:30:00.216 --> 00:30:02.051
that you wanted an army.

465
00:30:02.052 --> 00:30:03.886
Well. who doesn't these days?

466
00:30:03.887 --> 00:30:05.764
You Blackwoods certainly
never miss a chance

467
00:30:05.889 --> 00:30:09.808
to bloody your
swords... do you?

468
00:30:09.809 --> 00:30:11.018
Some 20 years ago.

469
00:30:11.019 --> 00:30:13.145
my lord bent the
knee to King Viserys

470
00:30:13.146 --> 00:30:16.441
and acknowledged the Princess
Rhaenyra as his rightful heir.

471
00:30:16.566 --> 00:30:18.276
Daemon: So you fight
for this old oath?

472
00:30:18.401 --> 00:30:21.571
Not. of course. for your
thousand-year-old feud with the Brackens.

473
00:30:23.114 --> 00:30:25.617
I once vied for Queen
Rhaenyra's hand...

474
00:30:26.242 --> 00:30:28.286
before she wed Ser Laenor.

475
00:30:28.787 --> 00:30:30.914
I always liked her spirit.

476
00:30:31.414 --> 00:30:33.290
She had the true
blood of the dragon.

477
00:30:33.291 --> 00:30:37.587
And you're prepared to march
without the leave of your lord...

478
00:30:39.589 --> 00:30:42.592
(ominous music playing)

479
00:30:43.593 --> 00:30:45.595
(eerie sounds)

480
00:30:57.774 --> 00:30:59.692
(pouring wine)

481
00:30:59.693 --> 00:31:01.653
Willem: Your Grace?

482
00:31:02.946 --> 00:31:04.488
And once you and your dragon

483
00:31:04.489 --> 00:31:07.826
bring the queen's justice
to the Brackens...

484
00:31:08.159 --> 00:31:10.370
our armies will be yours.

485
00:31:19.337 --> 00:31:22.007
Larys: Our lords in the
Crownlands are grousing.

486
00:31:22.132 --> 00:31:24.008
Their herds of livestock
struggle to keep pace

487
00:31:24.009 --> 00:31:25.634
with the dragons'
relentless appetites.

488
00:31:25.635 --> 00:31:28.178
- Vhagar's in particular.
- Ironrod: They can either provide

489
00:31:28.179 --> 00:31:31.306
the crown what it needs. or
we can claim their holdings.

490
00:31:31.307 --> 00:31:32.933
Tyland Lannister: Oh.
that would be a relief.

491
00:31:32.934 --> 00:31:35.352
as we have no more coin
to lend to the effort.

492
00:31:35.353 --> 00:31:37.646
Resources are certainly
growing no more plentiful

493
00:31:37.647 --> 00:31:39.189
in the face of the blockade.

494
00:31:39.190 --> 00:31:41.150
Tyland: The demand on the
blacksmiths. armorers and tanners

495
00:31:41.151 --> 00:31:42.526
for equipment has
only grown apace

496
00:31:42.527 --> 00:31:43.736
with Ser Criston's army.

497
00:31:43.737 --> 00:31:45.988
Ironrod: Well. Cole's done
splendidly. at the least.

498
00:31:45.989 --> 00:31:47.740
turning every castle
and army he's faced.

499
00:31:47.741 --> 00:31:51.035
- including Duskendale. gods bless him.
- (Aegon spinning marker)

500
00:31:51.036 --> 00:31:53.038
The Kingmaker.
they're calling him.

501
00:31:53.163 --> 00:31:55.289
And with Aemond and
Vhagar also at the ready.

502
00:31:55.290 --> 00:31:57.667
- we are a formidable opponent.
- (slams marker)

503
00:31:58.877 --> 00:32:00.670
You bore me.

504
00:32:03.548 --> 00:32:05.550
You all bore me.

505
00:32:13.933 --> 00:32:16.186
(door opens)

506
00:32:19.856 --> 00:32:23.984
- (door closes) - Perhaps Ser
Criston will be able to procure

507
00:32:23.985 --> 00:32:25.778
more livestock
through his campaign.

508
00:32:25.779 --> 00:32:29.074
Any coin we can save
will be a welcome bounty.

509
00:32:38.792 --> 00:32:40.085
What are you doing here?

510
00:32:40.210 --> 00:32:41.586
Where are your father's books?

511
00:32:41.711 --> 00:32:43.754
- Aegon Targaryen: I ordered them removed.
- (Alicent sighs)

512
00:32:43.755 --> 00:32:45.024
With no thought to the centuries

513
00:32:45.048 --> 00:32:46.674
of knowledge in those pages.

514
00:32:46.675 --> 00:32:48.760
(birds chirping)

515
00:32:53.431 --> 00:32:55.141
Your Grace.

516
00:32:56.393 --> 00:32:59.312
I removed them. I
didn't burn them.

517
00:33:04.484 --> 00:33:05.609
What is it?

518
00:33:05.610 --> 00:33:08.278
- They don't care what I think.
- (pouring wine)

519
00:33:08.279 --> 00:33:09.656
(sighs)

520
00:33:10.782 --> 00:33:13.033
- Who. Aegon?
- My council.

521
00:33:13.034 --> 00:33:15.160
Cole. Aemond. They
pursue their campaign

522
00:33:15.161 --> 00:33:17.580
without seeking my aid.
or even my thoughts.

523
00:33:20.583 --> 00:33:22.293
What thoughts would you have?

524
00:33:23.670 --> 00:33:25.588
Wh... I'm the king.

525
00:33:28.758 --> 00:33:32.470
Do you think simply wearing the
crown imbues you with wisdom?

526
00:33:38.435 --> 00:33:42.147
Those men at your
council table...

527
00:33:42.939 --> 00:33:44.941
earned their seats.

528
00:33:45.316 --> 00:33:48.527
It was my hope that
(chuckles) once enthroned.

529
00:33:48.528 --> 00:33:51.071
you would honor the
burden of your new duties.

530
00:33:51.072 --> 00:33:52.823
be silent.

531
00:33:52.824 --> 00:33:56.786
and strive to learn from the
more studied minds around you.

532
00:33:57.996 --> 00:34:01.374
In the hope that you might be
half the king your father was.

533
00:34:02.876 --> 00:34:05.462
- Tread carefully.
- Or what?

534
00:34:06.796 --> 00:34:10.008
You'll hang me. as you
did your ratcatchers?

535
00:34:10.133 --> 00:34:13.178
Or have me banished.
as you did your Hand?

536
00:34:14.137 --> 00:34:15.429
I ruled

537
00:34:15.430 --> 00:34:17.765
in your father's absence
throughout his long illness.

538
00:34:17.766 --> 00:34:20.517
and Otto Hightower was as cunning
a statesman as ever lived.

539
00:34:20.518 --> 00:34:26.149
You should humbly be seeking
our opinions and counsel.

540
00:34:28.193 --> 00:34:30.194
You have no idea the
sacrifices that were made

541
00:34:30.195 --> 00:34:33.155
to put you on that throne.

542
00:34:33.156 --> 00:34:36.409
(tense music playing)

543
00:34:37.202 --> 00:34:38.370
Wha...

544
00:34:40.372 --> 00:34:43.333
What would you
have me do. Mother?

545
00:34:44.334 --> 00:34:46.878
Do simply what is needed of you:

546
00:34:48.672 --> 00:34:50.173
nothing.

547
00:34:52.842 --> 00:34:54.844
♪

548
00:34:57.514 --> 00:35:00.767
(ambient nature sounds)

549
00:35:04.896 --> 00:35:06.564
(axe striking)

550
00:35:07.357 --> 00:35:09.526
(tree crackling)

551
00:35:15.865 --> 00:35:18.576
(indistinct chatter. shouting)

552
00:35:20.078 --> 00:35:22.372
Criston: On your feet!

553
00:35:23.373 --> 00:35:25.542
To Rook's Rest!

554
00:35:26.710 --> 00:35:28.253
To battle!

555
00:35:33.133 --> 00:35:34.883
Gwayne Hightower:
It's broad daylight.

556
00:35:34.884 --> 00:35:38.470
We must hold here and ready
ourselves to lay siege at nightfall.

557
00:35:38.471 --> 00:35:40.681
We shall move now
and strike by day.

558
00:35:40.682 --> 00:35:41.974
They will not expect it.

559
00:35:41.975 --> 00:35:43.267
They will not expect it

560
00:35:43.268 --> 00:35:45.603
because it is fucking madness.

561
00:35:47.272 --> 00:35:48.480
Did you forget the
little encounter

562
00:35:48.481 --> 00:35:50.483
we had on the road to Rosby?

563
00:35:51.067 --> 00:35:52.402
I did not.

564
00:35:53.945 --> 00:35:57.323
Dragonstone and their dragons
are just across the bay.

565
00:35:58.450 --> 00:36:00.660
What? Grown tired
of living. have you?

566
00:36:01.453 --> 00:36:03.329
Are you afraid. Ser?

567
00:36:04.122 --> 00:36:06.624
Worse. I'm rational.

568
00:36:08.626 --> 00:36:09.961
We advance.

569
00:36:10.420 --> 00:36:13.631
(tense music playing)

570
00:36:26.770 --> 00:36:28.772
♪

571
00:36:30.482 --> 00:36:32.066
Jacaerys Velaryon:
I see no other choice.

572
00:36:32.067 --> 00:36:34.861
- We need to send a dragon.
- Rhaenyra Targaryen: Where?

573
00:36:38.656 --> 00:36:40.783
(clears throat)
To support the war

574
00:36:40.784 --> 00:36:44.161
that your vassals have been
fighting in your absence...

575
00:36:44.162 --> 00:36:46.538
Your Grace.

576
00:36:46.539 --> 00:36:49.750
Cole's host has grown
since riding abroad.

577
00:36:49.751 --> 00:36:51.919
He raised the levies of
both Rosby and Stokeworth

578
00:36:51.920 --> 00:36:55.047
and. with their combined
strength. sacked Duskendale.

579
00:36:55.048 --> 00:36:56.757
Duskendale?

580
00:36:56.758 --> 00:36:58.592
The city has fallen.

581
00:36:58.593 --> 00:37:00.511
Many Darklyn men
declared for Aegon.

582
00:37:00.512 --> 00:37:02.681
Those who refused
were put to the sword.

583
00:37:02.806 --> 00:37:04.349
What of my father?

584
00:37:04.474 --> 00:37:05.892
He kept his oath.

585
00:37:06.351 --> 00:37:08.478
Cole took his head for it.

586
00:37:10.397 --> 00:37:13.190
Where have you been.
these last days?

587
00:37:13.191 --> 00:37:15.985
You vanished without
so much as a word.

588
00:37:16.528 --> 00:37:19.531
Well. I apologize for my
absence and the secrecy.

589
00:37:19.656 --> 00:37:22.408
but such was necessary.

590
00:37:22.409 --> 00:37:24.703
I went to King's Landing.

591
00:37:25.495 --> 00:37:27.162
To what possible end?

592
00:37:27.163 --> 00:37:29.456
To meet Queen Alicent
and sue for peace.

593
00:37:29.457 --> 00:37:32.251
- You saw Alicent?
- Rhaenyra: Yes. I did.

594
00:37:32.252 --> 00:37:34.546
You could've been
taken or slain!

595
00:37:34.671 --> 00:37:38.507
I inherited 80 years of
peace from my father.

596
00:37:38.508 --> 00:37:40.218
Before I was to end it.

597
00:37:40.343 --> 00:37:43.513
I needed to know that
there was no other path.

598
00:37:45.932 --> 00:37:47.684
And now I do.

599
00:37:51.104 --> 00:37:53.063
Only one choice remains to me:

600
00:37:53.064 --> 00:37:57.527
either I win my claim or die.

601
00:37:59.029 --> 00:38:01.239
We stand at the ready.

602
00:38:01.948 --> 00:38:04.324
Rhaenys Targaryen: Cole's
victories have only emboldened him.

603
00:38:04.325 --> 00:38:06.411
He marches on Rook's Rest.

604
00:38:06.536 --> 00:38:07.912
His host was just hours away

605
00:38:08.038 --> 00:38:11.248
- when Lord Staunton's ravens took wing.
- Why Rook's Rest?

606
00:38:11.249 --> 00:38:12.541
After Duskendale?

607
00:38:12.542 --> 00:38:14.668
It is but a small coastal keep.

608
00:38:14.669 --> 00:38:18.256
Alfred: 'Cause Lord Staunton
is a member of this council.

609
00:38:18.381 --> 00:38:22.427
And because his castle is small and
vulnerable and there for the taking.

610
00:38:22.552 --> 00:38:24.803
Cole knows we have no
army on the mainland.

611
00:38:24.804 --> 00:38:27.432
- Bartimos: He is brazen.
- He is daring us to act.

612
00:38:27.557 --> 00:38:30.476
We need to send a dragon.

613
00:38:30.477 --> 00:38:33.938
(quiet. tense music playing)

614
00:38:37.275 --> 00:38:41.738
There are those who have
mistaken my caution for weakness.

615
00:38:46.242 --> 00:38:49.036
Let that be their undoing.

616
00:38:49.037 --> 00:38:51.246
- I will go.
- My queen...

617
00:38:51.247 --> 00:38:54.125
- You cannot.
- I will not lose dragons to war

618
00:38:54.250 --> 00:38:55.459
whilst I hide here in my castle.

619
00:38:55.460 --> 00:38:58.587
Our allies raise their
banners for you. Mother.

620
00:38:58.588 --> 00:39:00.631
Rhaenyra: Yes. they do.

621
00:39:00.632 --> 00:39:03.926
If you die. all is lost.

622
00:39:03.927 --> 00:39:05.177
- Send me.
- No.

623
00:39:05.178 --> 00:39:07.221
I will burn Cole's lines and
withdraw before King's Landing

624
00:39:07.222 --> 00:39:09.599
- could even raise the alarm.
- You lack the experience.

625
00:39:12.352 --> 00:39:14.813
You must send me. Your Grace.

626
00:39:16.815 --> 00:39:18.315
Meleys is your largest dragon

627
00:39:18.316 --> 00:39:20.610
and no stranger to battle.

628
00:39:23.196 --> 00:39:25.031
I will meet Cole.

629
00:39:25.949 --> 00:39:27.074
(sighs)

630
00:39:27.075 --> 00:39:29.160
♪

631
00:39:48.972 --> 00:39:50.974
♪

632
00:40:13.329 --> 00:40:14.998
(flagon shatters)

633
00:40:16.374 --> 00:40:18.585
♪

634
00:40:33.558 --> 00:40:35.393
Jacaerys: I wish only
to fight for you.

635
00:40:35.518 --> 00:40:37.436
for your claim and mine.

636
00:40:37.437 --> 00:40:39.064
I...

637
00:40:40.231 --> 00:40:42.192
There's something I
need to tell you. Jace.

638
00:40:44.569 --> 00:40:47.905
Something... I
should've told you

639
00:40:47.906 --> 00:40:51.367
when you first became
heir to the throne.

640
00:40:51.368 --> 00:40:54.411
<i>It's a secret that
Viserys told me</i>

641
00:40:54.412 --> 00:40:56.873
<i>when he named me his successor.</i>

642
00:40:57.624 --> 00:41:00.877
<i>And it has passed
from king to heir...</i>

643
00:41:01.544 --> 00:41:04.589
<i>since Aegon the
Conqueror's time.</i>

644
00:41:06.966 --> 00:41:08.718
(exhales)

645
00:41:10.053 --> 00:41:12.055
♪

646
00:41:12.597 --> 00:41:14.848
<i>I never told you
because I was unsure</i>

647
00:41:14.849 --> 00:41:17.102
<i>that I believed it myself.</i>

648
00:41:17.936 --> 00:41:21.772
<i>The Targaryen who
sits the Iron Throne</i>

649
00:41:21.773 --> 00:41:24.316
<i>is not just a king or a queen.</i>

650
00:41:24.317 --> 00:41:26.652
<i>They are a Protector.</i>

651
00:41:26.653 --> 00:41:28.947
(speaking High Valyrian)

652
00:41:30.323 --> 00:41:32.658
Rhaenyra: <i>Ordained to
lead the Seven Kingdoms.</i>

653
00:41:32.659 --> 00:41:34.201
<i>to strengthen them...</i>

654
00:41:34.202 --> 00:41:36.537
(indistinct shouting)

655
00:41:36.538 --> 00:41:40.792
<i>and to unite them
against a common foe.</i>

656
00:41:45.088 --> 00:41:48.425
<i>Viserys chose me to succeed him.</i>

657
00:41:49.259 --> 00:41:52.177
<i>He held to this the
whole of his life.</i>

658
00:41:52.178 --> 00:41:53.972
(shouting)

659
00:41:57.642 --> 00:42:01.312
<i>My father believed
that I. alone.</i>

660
00:42:01.438 --> 00:42:03.897
<i>was meant to be this Protector.</i>

661
00:42:03.898 --> 00:42:07.151
They're 1.400-. 1.500-strong
at least. my lord.

662
00:42:07.152 --> 00:42:08.527
(roars)

663
00:42:08.528 --> 00:42:09.945
Rhaenyra: <i>But to
unite the realm.</i>

664
00:42:09.946 --> 00:42:12.866
<i>I had to send the
dragons to war.</i>

665
00:42:13.450 --> 00:42:14.950
(roars)

666
00:42:14.951 --> 00:42:16.995
♪

667
00:42:20.623 --> 00:42:24.669
The horrors I have just loosed
cannot be for a crown alone.

668
00:42:26.629 --> 00:42:28.630
<i>That is why I must believe</i>

669
00:42:28.631 --> 00:42:31.717
<i>what Viserys told me when
he named me his heir.</i>

670
00:42:31.718 --> 00:42:34.179
<i>What Jaehaerys had told him.</i>

671
00:42:34.846 --> 00:42:37.306
<i>And what I will now tell you.</i>

672
00:42:37.307 --> 00:42:39.351
(Sunfyre calls)

673
00:42:40.143 --> 00:42:41.143
What is it?

674
00:42:41.144 --> 00:42:43.188
♪

675
00:42:47.484 --> 00:42:49.819
Aegon the Conqueror's Dream.

676
00:42:51.738 --> 00:42:55.492
He called it "The
Song of Ice and Fire."

677
00:42:55.909 --> 00:42:59.578
- (dramatic music playing)
- (arrows whizzing by)

678
00:42:59.579 --> 00:43:01.873
(grunting. shouting)

679
00:43:05.251 --> 00:43:07.337
captain: Loose! New rank!

680
00:43:08.505 --> 00:43:11.675
Loose! New rank!

681
00:43:12.550 --> 00:43:15.053
Loose! New rank!

682
00:43:17.263 --> 00:43:19.556
♪

683
00:43:19.557 --> 00:43:20.850
Push it!

684
00:43:21.726 --> 00:43:23.561
guards (shouting): Dragon!

685
00:43:23.687 --> 00:43:25.730
Dragon!

686
00:43:25.855 --> 00:43:28.024
(all yelling)

687
00:43:29.734 --> 00:43:32.237
Gwayne: To the Seven
Hells with you. Cole!

688
00:43:32.570 --> 00:43:35.030
You may as well have sounded
horns to announce our coming!

689
00:43:35.031 --> 00:43:37.074
Criston: Order the Darklyn levies
to break off and move ahead.

690
00:43:37.075 --> 00:43:38.992
We must keep the dragon's
attention divided.

691
00:43:38.993 --> 00:43:41.036
- Make the signal.
- What signal?

692
00:43:41.037 --> 00:43:43.748
Criston: All is going to plan.

693
00:43:44.374 --> 00:43:46.376
♪

694
00:43:49.754 --> 00:43:51.965
(blows horn)

695
00:43:53.216 --> 00:43:54.926
(growling)

696
00:44:03.768 --> 00:44:05.937
(indistinct shouting)

697
00:44:10.108 --> 00:44:12.110
(all yelling)

698
00:44:15.655 --> 00:44:18.074
(horn blowing in distance)

699
00:44:19.242 --> 00:44:21.493
(blows horn)

700
00:44:21.494 --> 00:44:23.288
(growling)

701
00:44:27.250 --> 00:44:29.252
♪

702
00:44:32.922 --> 00:44:35.091
(Sunfyre calls)

703
00:44:37.427 --> 00:44:38.928
(groans)

704
00:44:40.513 --> 00:44:42.265
(speaking High Valyrian)

705
00:44:50.815 --> 00:44:52.525
(exhales)

706
00:44:54.152 --> 00:44:56.154
♪

707
00:44:56.821 --> 00:44:58.198
(screeches)

708
00:45:03.328 --> 00:45:04.996
(grumbles)

709
00:45:06.623 --> 00:45:08.833
(all yelling)

710
00:45:10.710 --> 00:45:13.296
♪

711
00:45:15.298 --> 00:45:16.757
Forward. Sunfyre!

712
00:45:16.758 --> 00:45:19.177
- (Sunfyre roars)
- Faster!

713
00:45:19.636 --> 00:45:21.637
guards (shouting): Dragon!

714
00:45:21.638 --> 00:45:23.682
Whose dragon is that?

715
00:45:23.807 --> 00:45:25.475
His Grace. the king's.

716
00:45:26.559 --> 00:45:28.686
This was your secret plot. Cole?

717
00:45:28.687 --> 00:45:30.312
For the king himself
to lay ambush

718
00:45:30.313 --> 00:45:32.731
- and mayhaps die in the attempt?!
- Criston: No!

719
00:45:32.732 --> 00:45:34.859
Loose more signal arrows!

720
00:45:38.029 --> 00:45:40.490
Stalwart men of House Targaryen.

721
00:45:41.658 --> 00:45:44.202
your king has joined you!

722
00:45:44.994 --> 00:45:47.746
Hold to your courage!
Hold to your wits!

723
00:45:47.747 --> 00:45:50.542
For the Seven have
blessed and shielded

724
00:45:50.667 --> 00:45:52.918
this host with divine purpose!

725
00:45:52.919 --> 00:45:55.880
For the one true king. Aegon!

726
00:45:56.006 --> 00:45:58.842
- Advance!
- (soldiers shouting)

727
00:46:00.510 --> 00:46:04.055
♪

728
00:46:06.725 --> 00:46:09.019
Where are you. Aemond?

729
00:46:12.230 --> 00:46:13.940
(roars)

730
00:46:15.400 --> 00:46:17.402
♪

731
00:46:20.697 --> 00:46:22.907
(speaks High Valyrian)

732
00:46:23.867 --> 00:46:25.452
<i>Dracarys!</i>

733
00:46:27.537 --> 00:46:28.872
(grunts)

734
00:46:31.875 --> 00:46:34.252
(grumbles. screeches)

735
00:46:37.964 --> 00:46:41.384
- (screeching. roaring)
- (Aegon panicking)

736
00:46:45.388 --> 00:46:47.098
(yelling)

737
00:46:51.394 --> 00:46:53.396
(all yelling)

738
00:46:57.650 --> 00:46:59.944
(high-pitched calling)

739
00:47:00.904 --> 00:47:02.572
(screeching)

740
00:47:04.282 --> 00:47:06.241
captain: Another one there!

741
00:47:06.242 --> 00:47:08.660
Send a volley to
those Rosby men!

742
00:47:08.661 --> 00:47:10.747
Give them no quarter!

743
00:47:11.623 --> 00:47:15.168
- (indistinct shouting)
- (distant bellowing)

744
00:47:20.090 --> 00:47:22.258
We'd best get you
to cover. my lord.

745
00:47:28.640 --> 00:47:30.642
♪

746
00:47:31.935 --> 00:47:33.645
(grumbles)

747
00:47:51.621 --> 00:47:54.540
♪

748
00:47:54.541 --> 00:47:56.543
(screeching)

749
00:48:06.886 --> 00:48:08.847
♪

750
00:48:08.972 --> 00:48:10.682
(distant screeching)

751
00:48:10.807 --> 00:48:12.976
Aegon: Thank the gods!

752
00:48:14.352 --> 00:48:15.519
<i>Dracarys!</i>

753
00:48:15.520 --> 00:48:16.563
Ah!

754
00:48:18.690 --> 00:48:20.191
♪

755
00:48:20.984 --> 00:48:23.319
No! (yells)

756
00:48:25.196 --> 00:48:28.074
- (roaring)
- (Sunfyre screeching)

757
00:48:34.831 --> 00:48:36.499
(screeching)

758
00:48:40.503 --> 00:48:42.504
(soldiers yelling)

759
00:48:42.505 --> 00:48:44.048
Criston: Your Grace!

760
00:48:44.049 --> 00:48:46.343
(music softens)

761
00:48:48.720 --> 00:48:50.722
(heavy breathing)

762
00:49:00.857 --> 00:49:02.776
(speaks High Valyrian)

763
00:49:04.402 --> 00:49:07.572
- (music intensifies)
- (Meleys screeches)

764
00:49:11.534 --> 00:49:12.702
(grunts)

765
00:49:23.755 --> 00:49:25.923
(nearby growling)

766
00:49:25.924 --> 00:49:28.093
♪

767
00:49:41.564 --> 00:49:43.566
(roars)

768
00:49:47.487 --> 00:49:50.073
- (dragons screeching)
- (music stops)

769
00:49:55.662 --> 00:49:56.830
(grunts)

770
00:49:58.456 --> 00:50:00.125
(grunting)

771
00:50:00.250 --> 00:50:02.626
(music resumes)

772
00:50:02.627 --> 00:50:04.504
(indistinct shouting)

773
00:50:18.601 --> 00:50:20.519
(all yelling)

774
00:50:20.520 --> 00:50:23.106
(grunting. yelling)

775
00:50:23.481 --> 00:50:26.359
- (horse neighs)
- (loud thud)

776
00:50:27.485 --> 00:50:29.195
(silence)

777
00:50:31.614 --> 00:50:36.161
- (slow-motion yelling)
- (slow. tense music playing)

778
00:50:39.664 --> 00:50:41.666
(loud footsteps)

779
00:50:54.471 --> 00:50:56.473
♪

780
00:51:00.977 --> 00:51:02.645
(grumbling)

781
00:51:08.401 --> 00:51:11.654
(Meleys grumbling. groaning)

782
00:51:19.704 --> 00:51:21.706
(singers vocalizing)

783
00:51:23.875 --> 00:51:25.585
(roars)

784
00:51:29.589 --> 00:51:32.509
(indistinct chatter. shouting)

785
00:51:33.176 --> 00:51:37.430
♪

786
00:51:39.015 --> 00:51:41.226
(vocalizing continues)

787
00:51:48.108 --> 00:51:49.859
(screeches)

788
00:51:52.112 --> 00:51:54.948
- (screeches)
- (all yelling)

789
00:51:57.200 --> 00:51:58.910
(screeching)

790
00:52:00.745 --> 00:52:02.455
(grunting)

791
00:52:02.747 --> 00:52:04.457
(screeching)

792
00:52:08.044 --> 00:52:09.962
(music slows)

793
00:52:09.963 --> 00:52:11.756
(grumbling)

794
00:52:15.885 --> 00:52:18.888
(somber music playing)

795
00:52:27.981 --> 00:52:29.733
(explosion booms)

796
00:52:37.073 --> 00:52:40.243
(triumphant music playing)

797
00:52:55.133 --> 00:52:57.344
(music fades out)

798
00:53:04.267 --> 00:53:06.436
(muffled yelling)

799
00:53:08.438 --> 00:53:11.316
(muffled roaring. rumbling)

800
00:53:21.284 --> 00:53:23.453
(gasps for air)

801
00:53:28.208 --> 00:53:29.793
(gasping)

802
00:53:34.130 --> 00:53:36.299
(labored breathing)

803
00:53:41.388 --> 00:53:44.808
(quiet. tense music playing)

804
00:53:50.480 --> 00:53:52.816
Gwayne: Fall in behind me!

805
00:53:53.817 --> 00:53:55.527
Into the breach!

806
00:53:55.652 --> 00:53:57.821
(indistinct shouting)

807
00:54:02.033 --> 00:54:04.035
♪

808
00:54:08.331 --> 00:54:10.542
(heavy breathing)

809
00:54:19.926 --> 00:54:21.928
♪

810
00:54:27.017 --> 00:54:29.853
(breathy) The king has
fallen. We must find him.

811
00:54:32.856 --> 00:54:34.858
(armor clatters)

812
00:54:43.366 --> 00:54:45.577
♪

813
00:54:54.377 --> 00:54:56.588
(indistinct shouting)

814
00:55:06.806 --> 00:55:08.808
♪

815
00:55:19.944 --> 00:55:21.154
Criston: Aemond!

816
00:55:22.113 --> 00:55:23.781
(Sunfyre grumbles)

817
00:55:23.782 --> 00:55:26.826
♪

818
00:55:36.586 --> 00:55:38.755
Where's His Grace?

819
00:55:41.299 --> 00:55:43.510
(Sunfyre grumbling)

820
00:55:45.845 --> 00:55:49.432
(suspenseful. solemn
music playing)

821
00:55:54.646 --> 00:55:56.606
(helmet clatters)

822
00:56:14.541 --> 00:56:16.960
(music fades out)

823
00:56:22.340 --> 00:56:25.719
(light. tense music playing)

824
00:56:59.878 --> 00:57:01.880
♪

825
00:57:35.080 --> 00:57:38.875
speaker: Behold!
The traitor dragon. Meleys.

826
00:57:40.251 --> 00:57:42.379
Slain by King Aegon!

827
00:57:44.089 --> 00:57:45.382
Alicent Hightower:
<i>Is he alive?</i>

828
00:57:46.257 --> 00:57:47.425
♪ (tense music plays)

829
00:57:47.550 --> 00:57:49.760
Rhaenyra Targaryen: <i>We cannot
challenge King's Landing</i>

830
00:57:49.761 --> 00:57:50.887
without the Riverlands.

831
00:57:51.096 --> 00:57:52.554
Daemon Targaryen:
Our terms are simple.

832
00:57:52.555 --> 00:57:55.433
Bend the knee to me.
or your house burns.

833
00:57:55.892 --> 00:57:59.312
mysterious voice: <i>Daemon. you
were made to wear a crown.</i>

834
00:58:00.438 --> 00:58:02.482
Otto Hightower: <i>The king
does not lack for heirs.</i>

835
00:58:02.774 --> 00:58:04.066
Alicent: <i>So. you
cast me aside?</i>

836
00:58:04.067 --> 00:58:05.859
We have given the
war to the dragons.

837
00:58:05.860 --> 00:58:07.570
<i>Will you preside over it?</i>

838
00:58:07.946 --> 00:58:09.048
Mysaria: <i>The people whispered.</i>

839
00:58:09.072 --> 00:58:10.907
when Viserys lived.
there was peace.

840
00:58:11.616 --> 00:58:13.326
The path I walk has
never been trod.

841
00:58:14.244 --> 00:58:16.955
Mysaria: <i>There is more than
one way to fight a war.</i>

842
00:58:18.081 --> 00:58:20.792
Ser Criston Cole: <i>What we
must do now is terrible.</i>

843
00:58:29.843 --> 00:58:32.302
(horns blare)

844
00:58:32.303 --> 00:58:35.015
♪ (tense music plays) ♪

845
00:58:37.475 --> 00:58:39.309
Ryan Condal: <i>Cole is
now a real problem</i>

846
00:58:39.310 --> 00:58:41.414
that's going to have to be
dealt with in the Crownlands.

847
00:58:41.438 --> 00:58:44.273
<i>He's taken down Duskendale.
and Rosby. and Darklyn.</i>

848
00:58:44.274 --> 00:58:45.941
and should be
marching on Harrenhal

849
00:58:45.942 --> 00:58:47.302
with the force that
he's assembled.

850
00:58:47.485 --> 00:58:49.653
Rhaenys Targaryen: Cole's
victories have only emboldened him.

851
00:58:49.654 --> 00:58:50.988
He marches on Rook's Rest.

852
00:58:50.989 --> 00:58:52.990
Rook's Rest. it's
a tiny coastal keep

853
00:58:52.991 --> 00:58:53.992
right across the bay.

854
00:58:54.159 --> 00:58:55.492
<i>Rhaenyra seizes upon that...</i>

855
00:58:55.493 --> 00:58:57.286
There are those
who have mistaken

856
00:58:57.287 --> 00:58:59.122
my caution for weakness.

857
00:59:00.331 --> 00:59:01.708
Let that be their undoing.

858
00:59:02.125 --> 00:59:03.543
And plays right
into Cole's hand.

859
00:59:03.710 --> 00:59:06.713
♪ (intense music plays) ♪

860
00:59:11.509 --> 00:59:12.676
George always said about Daemon.

861
00:59:12.677 --> 00:59:14.679
he's heroic and
villainous in equal parts.

862
00:59:14.846 --> 00:59:17.015
And that's what makes him
fascinating as a character.

863
00:59:17.182 --> 00:59:19.350
Part of Daemon's story
at Harrenhal this season

864
00:59:19.351 --> 00:59:23.563
is having to face and atone
for the sins of his past.

865
00:59:23.813 --> 00:59:24.856
<i>Laena.</i>

866
00:59:25.357 --> 00:59:27.525
Laena Velaryon: <i>Dracarys!</i>

867
00:59:29.527 --> 00:59:30.528
Ryan: <i>Aemond...</i>

868
00:59:31.363 --> 00:59:34.491
<i>who he probably had a hand.
a bit. in his creation.</i>

869
00:59:36.368 --> 00:59:38.912
And very much young Rhaenyra.

870
00:59:39.037 --> 00:59:41.498
(speaking in High Valyrian)

871
00:59:41.706 --> 00:59:42.706
Speak plainly.

872
00:59:42.916 --> 00:59:45.019
Matt Smith: <i>It's a journey
of discovery and unraveling.</i>

873
00:59:45.043 --> 00:59:49.005
and it's all beginning to make
him become really unstuck.

874
00:59:49.422 --> 00:59:51.674
Daemon is experiencing
one of his core injuries.

875
00:59:51.675 --> 00:59:54.009
This is the room that has
caused him so much pain.

876
00:59:54.010 --> 00:59:58.098
it's the seat that he's coveted
for so long and was denied.

877
00:59:58.390 --> 01:00:00.725
and then the little girl
who stole it from him.

878
01:00:00.934 --> 01:00:02.185
<i>Before he knows it...</i>

879
01:00:05.730 --> 01:00:06.856
he exacts vengeance.

880
01:00:07.065 --> 01:00:08.376
Matt: <i>It's the
blood of the dragon.</i>

881
01:00:08.400 --> 01:00:10.610
They're connected
in such a deep way.

882
01:00:11.111 --> 01:00:13.405
And the idea that
he could harm her

883
01:00:13.530 --> 01:00:15.573
<i>is. you know. really alien.</i>

884
01:00:15.865 --> 01:00:19.910
He's still very closed to
these intrusive visions.

885
01:00:19.911 --> 01:00:21.621
<i>but they start to break down</i>

886
01:00:21.746 --> 01:00:23.790
the very carefully
constructed walls

887
01:00:23.915 --> 01:00:25.625
that he's put up around himself.

888
01:00:27.752 --> 01:00:30.755
Touch late to be stalking
about a strange castle.

889
01:00:31.589 --> 01:00:33.967
Alys Rivers is written about
quite a bit in the book.

890
01:00:34.092 --> 01:00:35.969
She's described as a
kind of woods witch

891
01:00:36.094 --> 01:00:37.137
that lives at Harrenhal.

892
01:00:37.262 --> 01:00:39.221
has possibly been there
for hundreds of years.

893
01:00:39.222 --> 01:00:41.140
You don't really
know immediately

894
01:00:41.141 --> 01:00:44.394
whether she is what
she says she is.

895
01:00:45.228 --> 01:00:47.104
You are a strange kind of woman.

896
01:00:47.105 --> 01:00:49.607
I'm no woman at
all. I'm a barn owl.

897
01:00:49.941 --> 01:00:51.650
cursed to live in human form.

898
01:00:51.651 --> 01:00:53.068
Gayle Rankin: <i>She's
not afraid of him.</i>

899
01:00:53.069 --> 01:00:55.321
and I think that
he recognizes that.

900
01:00:55.447 --> 01:00:56.948
and that's unusual for him.

901
01:00:57.657 --> 01:00:59.659
Have you experienced
anything of note?

902
01:00:59.784 --> 01:01:03.496
She instills a sort of
curiosity in Daemon.

903
01:01:03.788 --> 01:01:07.000
What is she? Why is she
here? Is she influencing me?

904
01:01:07.125 --> 01:01:09.126
Am I beholden to her?

905
01:01:09.127 --> 01:01:10.794
She understands
things about him.

906
01:01:10.795 --> 01:01:13.172
whether because she's just
a good reader of people

907
01:01:13.173 --> 01:01:14.841
or there's something
else going on.

908
01:01:15.008 --> 01:01:18.260
and she penetrates him in a way
that I think fascinates him.

909
01:01:18.261 --> 01:01:19.678
but also makes him
very uncomfortable.

910
01:01:19.679 --> 01:01:21.430
Gayle: <i>I think it's
really up for debate</i>

911
01:01:21.431 --> 01:01:24.475
whether Alys is shaping
Daemon's journey.

912
01:01:24.476 --> 01:01:27.353
in terms of his kind
of spiritual awakening.

913
01:01:27.354 --> 01:01:29.689
<i>or if he's doing that himself.</i>

914
01:01:31.524 --> 01:01:32.609
(gulps)

915
01:01:34.444 --> 01:01:36.684
Aemond Targaryen: Ser Criston
is marching on Rook's Rest.

916
01:01:38.990 --> 01:01:41.451
The two of you
have been plotting

917
01:01:42.786 --> 01:01:44.287
without my authority.

918
01:01:44.954 --> 01:01:46.164
(sighs)

919
01:01:46.373 --> 01:01:48.142
Alan Taylor: <i>I love scenes
that involve Valyrian.</i>

920
01:01:48.166 --> 01:01:49.334
<i>It's a real language for us.</i>

921
01:01:49.626 --> 01:01:51.627
And the fact there are people
who speak it at different levels

922
01:01:51.628 --> 01:01:52.795
becomes part of their character.

923
01:01:52.796 --> 01:01:55.715
Aemond in this scene
is still furious at

924
01:01:55.840 --> 01:01:58.051
- his humiliation at the brothel.
- (laughter echoes)

925
01:01:58.718 --> 01:02:00.344
Aemond and Aegon
both. of course.

926
01:02:00.345 --> 01:02:01.804
learned High
Valyrian as children.

927
01:02:01.805 --> 01:02:04.516
It's just that Aemond paid a
little more attention to it.

928
01:02:05.058 --> 01:02:08.895
(speaking in High Valyrian)

929
01:02:09.521 --> 01:02:12.022
That scene is a public
execution. in a way.

930
01:02:12.023 --> 01:02:14.192
Only him and Aegon
can understand.

931
01:02:14.526 --> 01:02:15.984
<i>It's a public shaming.</i>

932
01:02:15.985 --> 01:02:19.239
(speaking in High Valyrian)

933
01:02:19.864 --> 01:02:21.509
Tom Glynn-Carney: <i>He's
aware that everyone else</i>

934
01:02:21.533 --> 01:02:23.909
<i>is feeling certain
resentment towards him.</i>

935
01:02:23.910 --> 01:02:25.704
but then when Aemond does it.

936
01:02:26.246 --> 01:02:28.707
that really breaks a
bit of his heart off.

937
01:02:29.207 --> 01:02:34.546
(speaking in High Valyrian)

938
01:02:38.341 --> 01:02:39.758
If there's one rule to take away

939
01:02:39.759 --> 01:02:41.844
from <i>House of the Dragon.</i>
don't laugh at Aemond.

940
01:02:41.845 --> 01:02:43.388
Bad things happen to you.

941
01:02:44.514 --> 01:02:46.433
They don't care what I think.

942
01:02:47.017 --> 01:02:48.017
(sighs)

943
01:02:48.226 --> 01:02:51.895
Alicent's just come off of
this near-assassination attempt

944
01:02:51.896 --> 01:02:53.063
with her head spinning.

945
01:02:53.064 --> 01:02:55.232
wondering whether
she misinterpreted

946
01:02:55.233 --> 01:02:57.068
what Viserys' final words were.

947
01:02:57.235 --> 01:02:59.737
And then she comes back home
and sees Aegon just. you know.

948
01:02:59.738 --> 01:03:02.282
stomping around and ranting
like a petulant teenager.

949
01:03:02.407 --> 01:03:05.743
My council. Cole. Aemond.
they pursue their campaign

950
01:03:05.744 --> 01:03:08.079
without seeking my aid
or even my thoughts.

951
01:03:08.455 --> 01:03:10.414
Contrary to many
people's beliefs.

952
01:03:10.415 --> 01:03:12.292
Aegon is a very
sensitive individual.

953
01:03:12.625 --> 01:03:15.628
<i>He wants his mom's love. He
wants his mom's validation.</i>

954
01:03:15.795 --> 01:03:17.964
He wants her to believe in him.

955
01:03:18.214 --> 01:03:22.092
Alicent can coat her words
in honey a little bit more

956
01:03:22.093 --> 01:03:24.137
to Aegon. if she chooses.

957
01:03:24.596 --> 01:03:28.099
But the tension is bubbling.

958
01:03:28.308 --> 01:03:29.600
Do you think simply
wearing the crown

959
01:03:29.601 --> 01:03:30.935
imbues you with wisdom?

960
01:03:31.478 --> 01:03:32.770
She's lost a bit
of the composure

961
01:03:32.771 --> 01:03:34.647
that you're used to
seeing in Alicent.

962
01:03:34.814 --> 01:03:36.607
and she simply
tells him. you know.

963
01:03:36.608 --> 01:03:38.651
you need to do what's
needed of you. which is...

964
01:03:38.777 --> 01:03:39.986
Nothing.

965
01:03:41.279 --> 01:03:44.907
And it's the most
devastating. most demeaning.

966
01:03:44.908 --> 01:03:46.909
belittling thing that she
could have said to her son

967
01:03:46.910 --> 01:03:47.910
in that moment.

968
01:03:47.994 --> 01:03:51.331
It's the first time we
see Alicent point-blank

969
01:03:51.956 --> 01:03:54.459
tell him everything
that he can't hear.

970
01:03:54.668 --> 01:03:57.420
Especially the way. how fragile
he is at that time. too.

971
01:03:57.921 --> 01:03:59.922
<i>And how he's just becoming
more and more naked</i>

972
01:03:59.923 --> 01:04:00.923
<i>and more and more alone.</i>

973
01:04:00.965 --> 01:04:02.676
And that's one of the
final straws for him.

974
01:04:02.801 --> 01:04:05.136
I think. before he
fully. fully spirals.

975
01:04:06.471 --> 01:04:07.681
(jug shatters)

976
01:04:08.431 --> 01:04:10.618
Ryan: <i>The thing that everybody
has warned Rhaenyra against is.</i>

977
01:04:10.642 --> 01:04:11.975
"You're the queen.
you're the sovereign.

978
01:04:11.976 --> 01:04:13.018
you cannot ride to battle."

979
01:04:13.019 --> 01:04:15.187
Aegon has just muscled
everybody out of the way

980
01:04:15.188 --> 01:04:16.548
and decided to ride
into the battle

981
01:04:16.606 --> 01:04:18.315
to prove that he was
just as much a man

982
01:04:18.316 --> 01:04:19.775
<i>as Cole and his brother.</i>

983
01:04:19.776 --> 01:04:22.529
(Sunfyre trills)

984
01:04:23.822 --> 01:04:25.614
Alan: <i>Cole has arrived
with his forces.</i>

985
01:04:25.615 --> 01:04:28.992
He's facing a tiny keep
that can't hope to win.

986
01:04:28.993 --> 01:04:30.285
Rook's Rest is really not

987
01:04:30.286 --> 01:04:32.371
a significant
strategic advantage.

988
01:04:32.372 --> 01:04:33.873
Why would Cole take that risk?

989
01:04:34.040 --> 01:04:36.000
<i>He never intends or
cares about the keep.</i>

990
01:04:36.001 --> 01:04:37.877
He's there to draw out a dragon.

991
01:04:38.169 --> 01:04:40.797
You must send me. Your Grace.

992
01:04:41.381 --> 01:04:42.841
I will meet Cole.

993
01:04:43.341 --> 01:04:45.175
Eve Best: <i>Rhaenys
chooses to step in.</i>

994
01:04:45.176 --> 01:04:47.512
<i>having said for
the whole season.</i>

995
01:04:47.679 --> 01:04:51.516
"We mustn't use dragons.
Anything but using dragons."

996
01:04:51.725 --> 01:04:55.687
If it has to be done. if
this action has to be taken.

997
01:04:55.812 --> 01:04:57.396
<i>then it's better
that she does it</i>

998
01:04:57.397 --> 01:04:58.565
<i>than anybody else.</i>

999
01:04:58.815 --> 01:05:02.152
Ultimately. she is expendable.
where Rhaenyra is not.

1000
01:05:02.694 --> 01:05:06.197
What should be a small
campaign to take a small keep

1001
01:05:06.364 --> 01:05:08.866
turns into a kind
of watershed moment.

1002
01:05:08.867 --> 01:05:10.076
soldier: Dragon!

1003
01:05:10.201 --> 01:05:13.204
Alan: <i>The first act of
full-on dragon conflict.</i>

1004
01:05:13.663 --> 01:05:16.540
- (Meleys screeching)
- (soldiers yelling)

1005
01:05:16.541 --> 01:05:18.167
<i>All bets are off.
All order is gone.</i>

1006
01:05:18.168 --> 01:05:19.918
Whatever you thought was
important on the battlefield

1007
01:05:19.919 --> 01:05:20.919
doesn't matter at all.

1008
01:05:20.920 --> 01:05:24.215
It's basically just a
collateral damage site

1009
01:05:24.758 --> 01:05:27.510
<i>because the real battle is
going on over your heads.</i>

1010
01:05:30.930 --> 01:05:32.222
(Sunfyre screeches)

1011
01:05:32.223 --> 01:05:35.059
Aegon has arrived as the fly
in the ointment. so to speak.

1012
01:05:35.060 --> 01:05:36.102
(frustrated grunt)

1013
01:05:36.269 --> 01:05:37.395
It's changed the strategy.

1014
01:05:37.604 --> 01:05:39.606
Now. Vhagar and Cole have
to contend with the fact

1015
01:05:39.731 --> 01:05:40.899
that the King is in the fray.

1016
01:05:41.024 --> 01:05:42.344
and they have to
protect the King.

1017
01:05:42.776 --> 01:05:43.943
Dracarys!

1018
01:05:45.528 --> 01:05:46.613
(Rhaenys grunts)

1019
01:05:47.781 --> 01:05:49.616
- (Meleys roars)
- (Sunfyre screeches)

1020
01:05:53.620 --> 01:05:54.980
Aegon II Targaryen:
Thank the gods!

1021
01:05:56.206 --> 01:05:57.415
Dracarys!

1022
01:05:57.707 --> 01:06:00.293
The question it raises.
did he seize an opportunity

1023
01:06:00.585 --> 01:06:02.419
where he could take two
players off the board.

1024
01:06:02.420 --> 01:06:04.588
<i>or was Aegon just collateral?</i>

1025
01:06:04.589 --> 01:06:05.799
(Aegon yells)

1026
01:06:07.133 --> 01:06:09.427
Tom: <i>When he's
plummeting to the earth</i>

1027
01:06:09.552 --> 01:06:11.262
<i>after being hit
by a ball of fire.</i>

1028
01:06:11.471 --> 01:06:14.890
all of his fears of
Aemon's betrayal...

1029
01:06:14.891 --> 01:06:16.893
- (Sunfyre screeches)
- <i>Come true.</i>

1030
01:06:18.395 --> 01:06:20.313
(soldiers yelling)

1031
01:06:20.438 --> 01:06:21.438
Criston Cole: Your Grace!

1032
01:06:21.439 --> 01:06:23.441
Of all the people
affected by this.

1033
01:06:23.817 --> 01:06:25.734
Cole is the one who's
most slammed by it

1034
01:06:25.735 --> 01:06:27.444
because it was his plan.

1035
01:06:27.445 --> 01:06:28.612
Cole has been in battle before.

1036
01:06:28.613 --> 01:06:29.655
He's seen people die.

1037
01:06:29.656 --> 01:06:31.073
He's seen people
crushed beneath horses.

1038
01:06:31.074 --> 01:06:33.493
<i>And so Cole had to be
particularly touched</i>

1039
01:06:33.618 --> 01:06:36.830
by the distinct and specific
nature of dragon war

1040
01:06:37.080 --> 01:06:39.290
and how insignificant
it made soldiers

1041
01:06:39.416 --> 01:06:41.126
<i>like him on the battlefield.</i>

1042
01:06:41.626 --> 01:06:44.462
He's playing chess and
messing with things

1043
01:06:44.671 --> 01:06:46.256
he can barely get
his head around.

1044
01:06:48.299 --> 01:06:50.010
(soldiers groaning)

1045
01:06:50.135 --> 01:06:54.764
It's the sort of moral
loss by his own actions.

1046
01:06:55.098 --> 01:06:57.350
Cole is responsible for
the worst possible thing

1047
01:06:57.475 --> 01:06:58.685
<i>that could have happened.</i>

1048
01:07:02.522 --> 01:07:04.649
- (Vhagar roars)
- (Meleys screeches)

1049
01:07:10.155 --> 01:07:12.281
Ryan: <i>I think it's a Pyrrhic
victory for both sides.</i>

1050
01:07:12.282 --> 01:07:13.700
We lose Rhaenys.

1051
01:07:13.825 --> 01:07:15.994
one of Rhaenyra's most
trusted counselors.

1052
01:07:16.786 --> 01:07:18.162
<i>We don't really
know the condition</i>

1053
01:07:18.163 --> 01:07:19.456
<i>of Sunfyre or Aegon.</i>

1054
01:07:19.789 --> 01:07:23.001
You just have to regard it
as a great emblem. an example

1055
01:07:23.126 --> 01:07:25.670
of how horrible and
awful dragon war is

1056
01:07:25.795 --> 01:07:27.714
and the reason that
it needs to be waged

1057
01:07:27.839 --> 01:07:29.382
<i>with great restraint.</i>

1058
01:07:29.507 --> 01:07:34.554
♪ (ominous music plays) ♪

